page.title: 16DIGSWELL LAKE
page.content:
I think Digswell Lake is very interesting because of all the nature.It is a very nice setting with lots of trees and flowers for the insects to live in.The reason we went to Digswell Lake was to study the birds there.We saw a Spotted Flycatcher,(which is very rare).We also saw moorhens,coots, and mallards.We got into groups and had Mums to lead us.As you can guess there is a lake there, in it are some water-boatman, I drew one.Once or twice we saw a pike, which is sometimes called'The Robber of the Water'.In groups we had things to do like Pond Dipping, Insect Finding and Going Bird Spotting.
{ALEXNDER WHYATT AND SAM GROSS (8) { {
